item.title: Path & class path
item.dc:creator: @cj_own_u cj own u
item.description:
@cj_own_u wrote:

well, when that happens to me, what i do is right click the icon, scroll down to “edit” open up that, then inside there will be something like

Java\jdk1.6.0_(number)

in there
or atleast

jdk1.6.0_(number)

and now where i have marked it (number) put in your version of jdk in it.

for example, mine is twelve, so mine would look like this

Java\jdk1.6.0_12

so yeah if yours is 12 put 12 in there, if not, then w/e it is.

hope that helped.
